This paper discusses transfer-learning and meta-learning approaches for custom model training, which are commonly used in machine learning and artificial intelligence research. The paper specifically focuses on few-class and few-shot target task settings, which are often studied in the sub-fields of machine learning and computer vision. Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-categories for this paper are cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.CV (Computer Vision), cs.CL (Computation and Language), and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
